learning_outcomes.en:
By finishing the course, the student: 
-	understands  letters of the Latin alphabet  (in particular letters with diacritic marks  and the digraphs) and reproduces the sounds of the Latin alphabet building a foundation for pronunciation and phonetic accuracy;
-	uses essential Bosnian vocabulary and basic grammar to communicate in everyday situations (greetings, introductions, ordering food, likes and dislikes);
-	recognizes and constructs simple affirmative, negative, and interrogative sentences in the present tense, identifies main and auxiliary verbs and uses common sentence structures;
-	reads and writes simple Bosnian texts on familiar topics using the Latin alphabet;
-	demonstrates familiarity with Bosnian cultural norms, values, and etiquette for respectful communication;
-	identifies and understands key Bosnian phrases in listening exercises and uses them accordingly in conversational practice.
